 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.5","title":"robot-redesign/incidents: durable escalation model for recurring operator pain","description":"Introduce a durable incident model for persistent and repeating problems such as crash loops, chronic rate limits, stale reservations, or long-lived stalls. This epic exists because transient alerts are not enough for operators to understand recurring pain or prioritize the work that keeps resurfacing.","design":"Incidents are meant to capture fingerprints, recurrence, severity, lifecycle state, and evidence links so that ntm can distinguish between one-off noise and real persistent operational trouble.\\n\\nThis is a controlled theft from vibe_cockpit's stronger escalation mindset, adapted to ntm's tmux-and-project workflow rather than to a fleet-monitoring worldview.","acceptance_criteria":"This epic is complete when repeated operational pain can be promoted, tracked, surfaced in snapshot/digest/attention, and closed explicitly instead of continually reappearing as disconnected warnings.","notes":"Incidents should help prioritize operator attention, not become a giant secondary ticketing system.","status":"open","priority":4,"issue_type":"epic","estimated_minutes":240,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:32:08.984551518Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T00:10:20.530945576Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["incidents","robot-redesign"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:32:08.984551518Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":317,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5","author":"ubuntu","text":"Future self: keep the incident model narrow and operator-focused. If it starts feeling like generic ITSM, you've gone too far.","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:32:09Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.5.1","title":"robot-redesign/incidents: define incident taxonomy and promotion rules","description":"Define which operator-visible problems stay as transient alerts and which ones should promote into durable incidents. This task exists so recurring or high-cost operational problems acquire lifecycle and memory instead of reappearing forever as disconnected warnings.","design":"The taxonomy should classify incident families such as crash loops, chronic quota pressure, repeated reservation conflicts, sustained stalls, unhealthy source outages, and broken coordination patterns. It should specify severity, promotion thresholds, deduplication/fingerprinting factors, resolution semantics, and how incidents relate to reason codes already used by attention and alerting.\\n\\nThe result should make incident behavior boring and predictable rather than heuristic folklore hidden in code.","acceptance_criteria":"Produce a self-contained incident taxonomy with promotion and resolution rules that downstream persistence and surface tasks can implement directly.\\n\\nThe taxonomy must explain what evidence accumulates an incident, what keeps it open, what resolves it, and how it differs from a momentary alert.","notes":"Incidents are worth adding only because they reduce operator cognitive load over time. If they become another noisy warning channel, this task failed.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":180,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:11.826693809Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T03:40:09.580941768Z","closed_at":"2026-03-22T03:40:09.580386218Z","close_reason":"Completed docs/incident-taxonomy.md - 16 families, promotion rules, lifecycle","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["alerts","incidents","robot-redesign"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:53.877190027Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:54.341697983Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:54.818470055Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.5","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:11.826693809Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":326,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.1","author":"ubuntu","text":"This bead captures a major architectural upgrade: ntm should remember persistent operator pain, not just report the latest symptoms.","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:12Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.5.2","title":"robot-redesign/incidents: implement incident persistence, fingerprinting, and lifecycle","description":"Implement persistent incidents with stable fingerprints, evidence accumulation, severity, status, and lifecycle transitions. This task exists to turn the incident model into a durable operational memory instead of a conceptual label.","design":"The implementation should define how incidents are keyed, how evidence is appended or summarized, how recurrence is tracked, how resolution and reopening behave, and how incidents connect to source_health, attention events, and runtime projections.\\n\\nThis task should also decide how much historical detail is kept directly on the incident versus in linked events, with a bias toward clear operator semantics over maximal logging.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when ntm can create, update, resolve, reopen, and query durable incidents with stable fingerprints and lifecycle semantics grounded in the taxonomy bead.","notes":"A strong implementation here makes later attention and digest outputs feel much smarter without requiring any hand-wavy 'AI insight' layer.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:13.201293920Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-23T03:11:55.136314769Z","closed_at":"2026-03-23T03:11:55.135806347Z","close_reason":"Completed: added durable incident fingerprint/family/category fields and migration, CreateOrUpdateIncident fingerprint lifecycle semantics, public GetIncidentByFingerprint queryability, reopen/new-after-window behavior with tests, and 7-day resolved-incident retention via RunGC.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["incidents","robot-redesign","sqlite"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:56.265139624Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:29.301037774Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.5","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:13.201293920Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:31.484489063Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"bd-j9jo3.5.3","title":"robot-redesign/incidents: integrate incidents into snapshot, digest, and attention","description":"Expose incidents as first-class operator-facing state inside the major robot surfaces. This task exists because incidents only pay off if they are visible in the places agents actually use to decide what to do next.","design":"The work should define how open incidents appear in snapshot, how newly promoted or changed incidents surface in digest, and how active incidents compete inside attention against transient alerts and coordination issues without letting duplicate churn drown the queue. It should also decide how repeated suppressed items or recurring failures graduate into incident evidence, how manual escalation or pinning interacts with incident priority, how operator snoozes avoid accidentally burying systemic problems forever, how resolved incidents are summarized without overwhelming the operator loop, and how recurrence remains visible even when attention is intentionally compacted. This task bridges durable operational memory into the surface layer.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when incidents are coherently represented across snapshot, digest, and attention with stable fields, reason codes, recurrence semantics, and prioritization behavior that work with both the attention-hygiene layer and operator override state rather than fighting them.","notes":"A future operator should be able to understand not just that something is wrong, but whether it is a persistent systemic problem that deserves heavier intervention.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":180,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:14.162114099Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T00:31:42.414340221Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["incidents","robot-redesign","surfaces"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:58.223677416Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:58.743011871Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:23:43.020340247Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:30:02.585430219Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.5","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:14.162114099Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:31.941442482Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:32.415339119Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"bd-j9jo3.5.3","title":"robot-redesign/incidents: integrate incidents into snapshot, digest, and attention","description":"Expose incidents as first-class operator-facing state inside the major robot surfaces. This task exists because incidents only pay off if they are visible in the places agents actually use to decide what to do next.","design":"The work should define how open incidents appear in snapshot, how newly promoted or changed incidents surface in digest, and how active incidents compete inside attention against transient alerts and coordination issues without letting duplicate churn drown the queue. It should also decide how repeated suppressed items or recurring failures graduate into incident evidence, how manual escalation or pinning interacts with incident priority, how operator snoozes avoid accidentally burying systemic problems forever, how resolved incidents are summarized without overwhelming the operator loop, and how recurrence remains visible even when attention is intentionally compacted. This task bridges durable operational memory into the surface layer.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when incidents are coherently represented across snapshot, digest, and attention with stable fields, reason codes, recurrence semantics, and prioritization behavior that work with both the attention-hygiene layer and operator override state rather than fighting them.","notes":"Operator checkpoint: incident plumbing is now wired through normalized promotion, durable incident upsert/reconciliation, snapshot active_incidents, digest active_incidents, and incident attention taxonomy/events. Added bounded reconciliation so promoted incidents auto-resolve when their source alerts no longer appear in the normalized projection. Focused robot-package verification is still running in a slow compile environment; do not close until the new incident-path tests/build return cleanly.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":180,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:14.162114099Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-23T06:57:08.694609895Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["incidents","robot-redesign","surfaces"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:58.223677416Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:58.743011871Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:23:43.020340247Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:30:02.585430219Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.5","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:14.162114099Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:31.941442482Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:32.415339119Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.5.4","title":"robot-redesign/incidents: implement bounded incident replay and as-of reconstruction","description":"Implement the bounded historical-replay capability that lets ntm reconstruct or serve a recent operator picture around an incident or requested timestamp without making operators manually stitch raw event history. This task exists because durable incidents and attention events are much more useful if ntm can replay them into a coherent as-of view for debugging, explanation, and post-mortem sharing.","design":"The implementation should build a bounded replay path on top of SQLite-backed projections, incidents, and attention events. It should decide when an as-of or incident replay is reconstructed from durable inputs versus served from a cached replay snapshot, what replay windows are kept, how cache invalidation and retention behave, how missing historical inputs are surfaced, and how replay outputs preserve stable identities, diagnostics handles, evidence links, and explicit degraded or partial markers.\n\nThis should stay tightly scoped to recent operational debugging and incident archaeology. It is not a general analytics engine. The product value is that an operator or agent can ask what ntm knew around this incident or timestamp and get a coherent, bounded, machine-readable answer quickly enough to use in live debugging and post-mortem work.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when ntm can provide bounded incident replay or recent as-of reconstruction with clear limits, stable references, explicit degraded markers, and enough caching or reconstruction discipline that the feature is practical rather than theoretical.","notes":"If the only historical debugging story is raw event replay, this task has not delivered the intended operator ergonomics.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-03-22T01:25:28.306561388Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T01:37:20.862098621Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["diagnostics","incidents","robot-redesign"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.13","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:26:03.700458231Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:26:04.490862733Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:26:05.326633241Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:30.170732411Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:26:06.148663572Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.5","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:25:28.306561388Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:26:07.009199162Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":351,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"Sensitivity follow-up: incident replay and as-of reconstruction must never resurrect raw secrets that were hidden in live flows. Historical answers need stable redaction markers, safe previews, and explicit explanations for why some evidence cannot be shown verbatim.","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:37:20Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.6","title":"robot-redesign/surfaces: rewrite robot outputs around shared projections","description":"Rewrite the major robot outputs so they all render from the shared projection model and the durable attention/incidence state. This epic exists to replace overlapping command-local dumps with fewer stronger surfaces whose responsibilities are obvious to both humans and agents.","design":"The central move is to make snapshot the bootstrap contract, status the cheap summary, attention/digest the delta and action queue, and targeted inspect surfaces the drill-down path. Those surfaces should share section boundaries and next-action semantics rather than inventing different summaries for every transport.\\n\\nThis epic also owns renderer alignment: JSON, TOON, markdown, and terse outputs should describe the same section model with format-specific compression, not format-specific semantics.","acceptance_criteria":"This epic is complete when the operator loop is coherent, section-aligned, and clearly superior to the current command-local assembly style.","notes":"Do not add a new top-level overview command by reflex. First make snapshot truly worthy of its bootstrap role.","status":"open","priority":4,"issue_type":"epic","estimated_minutes":360,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:32:10.227193801Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T00:10:20.607626763Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["robot-redesign","surfaces"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:32:10.227193801Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":318,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6","author":"ubuntu","text":"Future self: every new surface must justify its existence against the question 'why isn't this a better section or mode of snapshot/status/attention/digest?'","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:32:11Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.6.1","title":"robot-redesign/surfaces: rewrite snapshot as the canonical bootstrap surface","description":"Rewrite --robot-snapshot so it becomes the single authoritative bootstrap surface for agents and other machine consumers. This task exists because bootstrap currently leaks across overlapping commands and ad hoc assembly paths.","design":"The new snapshot should project directly from the shared runtime model and include the canonical sections needed to orient an operator: summary, sessions, work, coordination, quota, alerts, incidents, attention summary, source_health, replay or cursor information, next_actions or equivalent action hints, and compact explanation handles or evidence references that point to deeper diagnostics when data are stale, degraded, truncated, or incident-heavy.\n\nIt must be rich enough to initialize an operator loop without requiring follow-up calls just to understand the current system state, while still making clear when inspect or diagnostics drill-down is the right next step.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when snapshot is the clearly documented bootstrap surface, uses explicit payload schema identity, and projects from shared runtime sections instead of reassembling state directly from live sources.","notes":"This is intentionally not a new overview command. The goal is to make snapshot excellent enough that no overview sibling is needed.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":240,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:15.116946064Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T01:37:21.656007258Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["robot-redesign","snapshot","surfaces"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:01.346887815Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:47:57.454986793Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:57:21.992593791Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:02:33.267400943Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.8","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:10:25.053817649Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.9","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:17:47.930311862Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:59.250258801Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:59.759158095Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:31.041599554Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:00.292252256Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:00.835782110Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:15.116946064Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":327,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.1","author":"ubuntu","text":"Snapshot is where the redesign cashes out for first-contact ergonomics. If a fresh agent still feels lost after reading it, this task is not done.","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:16Z"},{"id":352,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.1","author":"ubuntu","text":"Sensitivity follow-up: snapshot must surface disclosure-control markers and safe-preview semantics clearly enough that a first-contact agent understands when evidence is present but transformed, rather than mistaking redaction for missing data.","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:37:21Z"}]}

